Sentencas: The high co-sintering temperature of BZCYYb electrolyte membranes supported by anode substrates usually causes a series of problems including undesirable electrolyte-anode reactions/diffusion and Ba-evaporation, posing a challenge for seeking alternative fabrication approaches.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, BZCYYb electrolyte membranes supported by anode substrates are fabricated by a large-scale and cost-effective atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) process.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 25 pm thick BZCYYb membrane has negligible electrolyte-anode reactions/diffusion due to the APS process free of high-temperature co-firing.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ba-evaporation problem is also resolved during APS process because of the adoption of large-grained BZCYYb feedstock powders.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After 15 cycles of postdensification treatment by infiltrating, the plasma-sprayed BZCYYb membrane is dense enough for electrolyte application.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell based on dense plasma-sprayed BZCYYb electrolyte membrane shows a peak power density of 0.35 W cm(-2) at 750 degrees C using 3 vol% humidified H-2 as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Atmospheric plasma-sprayed BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ (BZCYYb) electrolyte membranes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
